      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"Samsung 860 EVO SSD experiences queued TRIM (FPDMA SEND DSM) timeouts with ASMedia ASM1062 controller. The kernel uses a device blacklist (ata_device_blacklist array in libata-core.c) to apply hardware-specific workarounds via horkage flags. Samsung SSD 840 and 850 models are already blacklisted with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM to disable queued TRIM support due to similar issues. The Samsung 860 EVO is missing from this blacklist, causing it to attempt queued TRIM operations which fail with timeout errors. The fix requires adding a blacklist entry for Samsung SSD 860* with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag (and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM as used by other Samsung SSDs) to prevent queued TRIM usage. This flag clears the DSM TRIM bit in ncq_send_recv_cmds during ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() (line 2218-2221), causing ata_fpdma_dsm_supported() to return false and forcing use of non-queued TRIM commands instead.\"\n}\n",
